task.summary: Added core navigation with routes along with Bootstrap and Jinja templates
Moved to AngularJS 1.5.8 for serving the content. Added UI-router and Angular-Breadcrumbs dependencies.
Got rid of jQuery in favor of Angular-Bootstrap. Updated project structure & miscellanous tweaks.
Removed ng-include for nav element because of triggering unwanted animations (ui-bootstrap issue #5474). Introduced the "Dataset" class in backend.
In-between scanpath similarity calculation (edit distance) added to backend.

Changed data structure, introduced Environment class
Each experiment (or dataset) now has its own scanpaths+regions+visuals folders containing related data. All python sources were moved to src folder.
Environment class stores the parameters affecting eye tracking measurements such as screen resolution, distance from eyetrecker and the like. It is also used for computing the error area and screen PPI.

Implemented similarity calculations
Other minor improvenemts. Refactoring needed ($scope should be able to access scanpaths directly by given identifier - store as an object instead of simple array)

Minor JS tweaks.
Refactoring & TODOs implementation still needed.
Minor code refactoring and small bug fixes
Separated angular controllers from app declaration
